node.text:
Do you sometimes feel invisible? 

When you don’t see yourself, who you are and who you want to be in the media. 

Today, less than one in five of us believe ads are representative of wider society and almost one in two from under-represented communities feel stereotyped through advertising. 

If you’re not including, you’re excluding. 

So we’re taking action to make all marketing inclusive marketing. And we’re starting with us. With #Act2Unstereotype. 

We’re making real, structural changes to our entire marketing process to ensure diversity, equity and inclusion are embedded at every point of the end-to-end marketing journey. 

From insight generation to the way we brief product design to the way we represent people in front of and behind the camera. 

Tap the link in our bio to find out more.

#Unstereotype
Where are those with use of a mobility aid in their everyday life 😢
Great Ad campaign hope communities will embrace it
